This is a speech given by President Trump at MacDill Air Force Base in Tampa, Florida. He begins by thanking the military leaders and coalition partners in attendance. He also acknowledges Governor Rick Scott and expresses gratitude to the military families and spouses. President Trump promises to provide the military with the necessary tools and resources, while also ensuring that taxpayer dollars are not wasted. He emphasizes the importance of NATO members paying their fair share. He praises the bravery and dedication of those serving in CENTCOM and SOCOM in the fight against radical Islamic terrorism. President Trump states that the US will defeat ISIS and radical Islamic terrorism and will not allow it to take root in the country. He concludes by expressing support for the military and the mission for peace through strength.